      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Bring chicken stock, coriander, cumin and chili powder to a simmer in small pot"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Chop 3 of the roasted red peppers, add 1-2 tbsp of liquid to chicken stock"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Heat heavy bottomed pan over medium-high heat, add oil and butter"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Once butter stops foaming, add leeks and saute 5 minutes"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add garlic and rice, cook 1 minute, stirring constantly"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add 1 cup of simmering stock and chopped red peppers, reduce heat to medium, stirring frequently"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Continue adding 1/2 cup of stock at a time once liquid is almost absorbed until rice is tender"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Remove from heat and stir in cheese, serve immediately"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "To add flair… half and clean out a pepper, stuff with risotto, put grated cheese on top and bake until pepper is soft"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "If something goes wrong",
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "Risotto is gluey",
              "cause": "Over-stirred, or too much rice for the stock.",
              "fix": "Stir less. The agitation releases starch — you want some, but not all of it. Add a splash more stock at the end to loosen."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Rice still has a hard core",
              "cause": "Stock added too cold, or undercooked.",
              "fix": "Keep the stock at a simmer in a separate pan while you cook. Add another ladle and keep going — the rice tells you when it's done."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Risotto is too soupy",
              "cause": "Last addition of stock was too much.",
              "fix": "Take the pan off the heat, beat in cold butter (mantecare), and let it stand for two minutes. It firms up as it rests."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Tastes bland",
              "cause": "Stock was weak, or no finishing fat.",
              "fix": "Beat in cold butter and a fistful of grated parmesan off the heat. The fat carries the flavour."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Mushroom: add 30 g dried porcini soaked in warm water; use the soaking liquid as part of the stock."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Seafood: stir through cooked prawns and a handful of peas in the last two minutes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Where this dish lives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The dish sits in the Italian home-cooking tradition: a few good ingredients, a long unhurried cook, and a pan that has fed the family for years. Worth keeping its roots in mind when you taste — the silence between flavours is part of the design."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
